cff-version: 1.2.0
title: OpenBioHack
message: >-
  If you use OpenBioHack in your work, or build on it, please cite it using
  the metadata below.
type: software
authors:
  - given-names: Matteo
    family-names: Trevisan
    alias: Teo Embers
abstract: >-
  OpenBioHack is a free, open-source, first-principles thinking partner for hard,
  ambiguous health problems and for health optimization. It runs inside Claude Code
  on the user's own data, working backward from lived experience to the biological
  processes that could be producing it (or forward from a desired state to its
  requirements), and surfaces low-risk, reversible possibilities to consider and
  discuss with a qualified clinician. It is an educational and research tool, not a
  medical device, and produces no medical advice or diagnosis. Non-directive by
  design.
keywords:
  - health
  - biohacking
  - quantified-self
  - personal-health
  - claude-code
  - claude-skill
  - ai-agent
license: Apache-2.0
repository-code: 'https://github.com/OpenBioHack/openbiohack'
